  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Configurations provide a lightweight way to apply content and styling to views without having to manage the rendering of the appearance yourself."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Using a configuration, you can obtain system default styling for a variety of different view states and customize that styling as needed. Then, you assign that configuration to a view that supports configurations, like "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uicollectionviewcell"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", or use it to create a custom content view, like "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uilistcontentview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". The configuration updates itself when the view’s configuration state changes, causing the view to reflect the new styling for that state."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "There are two types of configurations:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Background configurations, which let you specify background appearance for a view. For more information, see "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uibackgroundconfiguration"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ". "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Content configurations, which let you specify content (like image and text) and styling for that content (like tint color and padding). For list-based content, "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uilistcontentconfiguration"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " defines many customization options."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
